\f3\i \cf0 *A note about video players
\f2\i0 : If the video is a .mp4 file, both QuickTime (usually the default program) and iTunes will play the video correctly at 5x speed. Both file types can also be opened in VLC player, but VLC cannot exceed 4x playback. If the video is a .mpg file, open with iTunes (because as of 2020, .mpg files accelerated to 5x speed in QuickTime play back at a different speed), or check to see if this bug has been fixed.
